üåü What is the experiment for?

This experiment is done to create a simple web application using the Spring MVC framework.
It teaches you how to separate the work of a web application into Model, View, and Controller for easy development.


---

üìù Procedure in simple full sentences

1. First, open the STS or Eclipse IDE on your computer.


2. Create a new Maven project and select WAR as the project type.


3. Open the pom.xml file and add the Spring MVC and servlet dependencies.


4. Create a controller class called HomeController.java to handle the main website request.


5. Write the @RequestMapping code inside the controller to connect the URL to the page.


6. Create a home.jsp file inside the WEB-INF/views folder to display the message on the screen.


7. Create a dispatcher-servlet.xml file to set up the Spring MVC configuration.


8. Add the web.xml file to connect the DispatcherServlet to your project.


9. Finally, run the project on the Apache Tomcat server and open the browser to see the output.




