üåü Experiment Name

Build a simple web application using the Spring MVC pattern.


---

üåü Aim

To create a small web application using the Spring MVC model‚Äìview‚Äìcontroller pattern.


---

üåü Tools Required

JDK 17 or above ‚Äì to run Java programs.

Apache Tomcat ‚Äì to run the web application.

Spring Framework ‚Äì to build the MVC app.

Maven ‚Äì to add libraries easily.

IDE (Eclipse/STS/IntelliJ) ‚Äì to write and run the code.



---

üåü Theory (Very Simple Words)

What is Spring MVC?

Spring MVC is a framework that helps you build web applications in a clean and organized way.

Three Main Parts:

1. Model ‚Äì holds data and logic.


2. View ‚Äì shows the output on the screen (like JSP pages).


3. Controller ‚Äì receives user requests and decides what to show.



How Spring MVC Works (Simple Flow):

1. The user sends a request from the browser.


2. The request first goes to DispatcherServlet.


3. DispatcherServlet sends it to the Controller.


4. Controller prepares data using the Model.


5. The ViewResolver picks the correct JSP page.


6. The page (View) is shown to the user.




---

üåü Code Explanation (Simple Words)

pom.xml

This file adds Spring MVC and servlet libraries needed for the project.

HomeController.java

This file receives the request and sends a message to the JSP page.

dispatcher-servlet.xml

This file tells Spring where to find controllers and how to load JSP pages.

home.jsp

This is the webpage that shows the message.

web.xml

This file connects the DispatcherServlet to your project so it can handle all requests.


---

üåü Expected Output

The browser shows the message:
‚ÄúWelcome to Spring MVC Web Application!‚Äù


---

üåü Result

The Spring MVC web application works successfully and displays the output.
